{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "pi-vimmode already supports prompt-local line transforms through Ex commands: `:indent` adds two spaces to addressed lines and `:dedent` removes at most one tab, two spaces, or one leading space. The missing Vim-fluent surface is the normal/visual shift operator keys `>` and `<`. The implementation crosses the semantic key parser, keymap config, modal side effects, repeat state, pure prompt-buffer transforms, tests, and docs. The main constraint is keeping this as finite prompt editing, not open"}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Support normal-mode `>>` and `<<` for current-line indent/dedent."}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Decision 1: Model shifts as semantic line-only operators Add `indent` and `dedent` to the semantic operator action set with default bindings `>` and `<`."}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_decision_1_model_shifts_as_semantic_line_only_operators", "label": "Decision 1: Model shifts as semantic line-only operators", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 27", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Add `indent` and `dedent` to the semantic operator action set with default bindings `>` and `<`. Target seams:"}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_decision_2_keep_shift_operators_line_only_in_the_parser", "label": "Decision 2: Keep shift operators line-only in the parser", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 49", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`indent` and `dedent` SHALL only resolve as line commands when the configured operator sequence is repeated. Unsupported combinations such as `>w`, `>iw`, `>/query`, and `>'a` must clear pending state without editing prompt text or inserting the key. Target seams:"}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_decision_3_reuse_prompt_transform_operations_through_a_small_line_shift_helper", "label": "Decision 3: Reuse prompt transform operations through a small line-shift helper", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 68", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Implement normal and visual shifts by resolving a line range and calling the existing prompt transform path with `{ action: \"indent\" }` or `{ action: \"dedent\" }`. Target seams:"}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_decision_4_expose_keymap_config_but_keep_operator_motions_scoped", "label": "Decision 4: Expose keymap config but keep operator motions scoped", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 98", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Add default operator bindings: - `piVimMode.keymap.operators.indent`: `[\">\"]`"}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 126", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- **Risk: New operator actions leak into delete/change/yank paths** \u2192 Mitigate with parser-level line-only gating plus defensive modal guards and regression tests for `>w`, `>iw`, `>/query`, and `>'a`. - **Risk: Config propagation drift** \u2192 Mitigate by updating `src/config.ts` clone/default/merge paths and adding live editor or parser/config tests proving configured shift bindings work. - **Risk: Behavior drift between Ex transforms and shift operators** \u2192 Mitigate by delegating to `applyPromptT"}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 134", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- No data migration or dependency change. - Implement behind the existing keymap/config surfaces. - Rollback is removal of the added semantic operators, parser branches, modal shift handling, tests, and docs."}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_open_questions", "label": "Open Questions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 141", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "None. Scope is intentionally limited to line shifts and visual selected-line shifts."}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_ref_src_types_ts", "label": "types.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 33", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_ref_src_config_ts", "label": "config.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 34", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_ref_src_commands_ts", "label": "commands.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 35", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_ref_src_modal_types_ts", "label": "types.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 36", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_document", "target": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_document", "target": "2026_06_02_add_shift_operators_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-02-add-shift-operators/design.md", "source_location": "line 7",